\par Epic characters\emdash those whose character level is 21st or higher\emdash are handled slightly differently from nonepic charact
ers. While epic characters continue to receive most of the benefits of gaining levels, some benefits are replaced by alternative gains. A class can be advanced beyond 20}{\fs20\cf0\super th}{\fs20\cf0 
 level.  A ten-level prestige class can progress beyond 10}{\fs20\cf0\super th}{\fs20\cf0  level, but only if the character level is already 20}{\fs20\cf0\super th}{\fs20\cf0 
 or higher.  A class with fewer than ten levels cannot progress beyond the maximum for that class, regardless of character level.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Epic Save Bonus:}{\fs20\cf0  A character\rquote s base save bonus does not increase after character level reaches 
20th. However, the character does receive a cumulative +1 epic bonus on all saving throws at every even-numbered level beyond 20th, as shown on Table: Epic Save and Epic Attack Bonuses. Any time a feat, prestige class, or other rule refers to your base sa
ve bonus, use the sum of your base save bonus and epic save bonus.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Epic Attack Bonus:}{\fs20\cf0  Similarly, the character\rquote s base attack bonus does not increase after character level reaches 20th. However, the character does receive a cumulative +1 epic bonus on all a
ttacks at every odd-numbered level beyond 20th, as shown on Table: Epic Save and Epic Attack Bonuses. Any time a feat, prestige class, or other rule refers to your base attack bonus, use the sum of your base attack bonus and epic attack bonus.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Class Skill Max Ranks:}{\fs20\cf0  The maximum number of ranks a character can have in a class skill is equal to his or her character level +3. 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Cross-Class Skill Max Ranks:}{\fs20\cf0  For cross-class skills, the maximum number of ranks is one-half the maximum for a class skill. 
\par Feats: Every character gains one feat (which may be an epic or nonepic feat at the player\rquote s choice) at every level divisible by three. These feats are in addition to any bonus feats granted in the class descriptions. 
\par Ability Increases: Upon gaining any level divisible by four, a character increases one of his or her ability scores by 1 point. The player chooses which ability score to improve. For multiclass characters, feats and ability increases are gained according 
to character level, not class level. 
